nameLink u-textInheritColor js-nav" href=3D"https://twitter.com/eqx1979" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">Chrysanthe Tenentes</a> will be=
 guest-hosting the site. I am a huge fan of the Kottke guest editor progra=
m &mdash;&nbsp;starting eight years ago=2C it quite literally changed my l=
ife &mdash;&nbsp;and I&#39;m looking forward to reading Chrysanthe&#39;s v=
ersion of the best blog in the universe.</p>

<h2 style=3D"color: #F00A0A;font-size: 22px;line-height: 27px;font-weight:=
 bold;margin: 35px 0 10px;">&quot;Every breath you take is mercy from me&q=
uot;</h2>

<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">Hold on; it turns out I&#39;m <a href=3D"ht=
tps://kottke.org/18/02/a-short-melancholy-review-of-black-panther" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">not done thinking=
 about <em>Black Panther</em></a>. (It&#39;s still the biggest movie going=
=2C and one of the biggest of all time=2C so we can all be forgiven.) I sa=
w it again=2C and I&#39;m still convinced the key line in the film is T&#3=
9;Challa&#39;s &quot;every breath you take is mercy from me&quot; &mdash;&=
nbsp;spoken to Klaw (but not just to Klaw; it&#39;s really T&#39;Challa&#3=
9;s attitude towards the entire world).</p>

<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">I also happen to know that this line is a l=
ift from the comics=2C specifically New Avengers vol. 3=2C no. 22=2C writt=
en by Jonathan Hickman. (Consider New Avengers added to the <a href=3D"htt=
ps://kottke.org/18/02/black-panther-a-suggested-comics-reading-list" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">recommended comic=
s reading list for Black Panther</a>.) There=2C T&#39;Challa says it to Na=
mor=2C whom he&#39;s also intent on killing in retribution for murdering W=
akandans. And there=2C the line concludes=2C &quot;... And I&#39;m all out=
=2E&quot;</p>

<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;"><img data-file-id=3D"901635" src=3D"https:/=
/gallery.mailchimp.com/f2ef8dc4cb32880aecd8d6730/images/1e05c9a7-a1f5-461c=
-a746-be1ada509eb3.jpg" style=3D"border: 0px;width: 1000px;margin: 0px;lin=
e-height: 100%;outline: none;text-decoration: none;max-width: 100%;height:=
 auto;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;" width=3D"1000"></p>

<p class=3D"image-caption" style=3D"margin: -15px 0 25px;color: #666666;fo=
nt-size: 16px;line-height: 22px;">New Avengers 22=2C art by Kev Walker</p>

<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">It seems important that Black Panther is a=
 superhero who is willing to kill but prefers not to. Usually=2C superhero=
es are either killing people almost all the time (Logan=2C Deadpool=2C etc=
=2E)=2C or they&#39;ve sworn never to kill anyone (Batman=2C Spider-Man=2C e=
tc.). Wonder Woman is one of the only other heroes who&#39;s ready and wil=
ling to use deadly force in extraordinary circumstances=2C but is generall=
y bent on saving people rather than killing them.</p>

<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">Part of what this does is it makes Black Pa=
nther&#39;s mercy <em>mean</em> something. He saves=2C and offers to save=
=2C people he has every reason to kill. He&#39;s appalled by his father&#3=
9;s lack of mercy &mdash;&nbsp;not so much for killing his own brother=2C=
 but for abandoning his brother&#39;s son (and in a larger sense=2C all of=
 Wakanda&#39;s lost children). T&#39;Challa is a man who will not waste a=
 single Wakandan=2C who would never give up a single Wakandan life. This i=
s his strongest contrast with Killmonger/N&#39;Jadaku=2C who treats every=
 Wakandan (in fact=2C every person=2C including the black people of the di=
aspora he claims to champion) as totally disposable.</p>

<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">So what we get with T&#39;Challa is a doctr=
ine of <a href=3D"https://longreads.com/2018/02/22/how-black-panther-asks-=
us-to-examine-who-we-are-to-one-another/" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000;font-weight: bold;">radical mercy</a>. He could kill all his ene=
mies. He doesn&#39;t. He saves them. And <a href=3D"https://www.gq.com/sto=
ry/black-panther-and-the-search-for-home" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000;font-weight: bold;">more than once</a>=2C that saves him.</p>

<h2 class=3D"null" style=3D"color: #F00A0A;font-size: 22px;line-height: 27=
px;font-weight: bold;margin: 35px 0 10px;">In case you haven&#39;t had eno=
ugh</h2>

<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">There&#39;s a terrific <a href=3D"https://k=
ottke.org/18/02/profile-of-21-year-old-film-student-ryan-coogler" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">decade-old profile=
 of BP director Ryan Coogle</a>r when he was still a film student. There&#=
39;s a <a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/02/fahrenheit-451" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">trailer for <em>Fahrenheit=
 451</em></a><em>=2C</em> with <em>Creed</em>/<em>Black Panther</em> star=
 Michael B. Jordan. And there&#39;s a <a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/02/=
the-cool-futuristic-typeface-from-the-black-panther-ending-credits" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">closer look at the=
 typeface</a> used in BP&#39;s closing credits. Ah; we covered the story=
=2C the filmmaker=2C actors=2C and design. That works out quite neatly.</p=
>

<h2 class=3D"null" style=3D"color: #F00A0A;font-size: 22px;line-height: 27=
px;font-weight: bold;margin: 35px 0 10px;">I&#39;m only here for the fonts=
</h2>

<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">I think you mean typefaces=2C but I got you=
=2E There are a full eight in use on <a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/02/all=
-the-typefaces-used-on-the-iconic-huy-fong-sriracha-label" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">the iconic Huy Fong srirach=
a hot sauce label</a>=2C not counting the icon of the rooster. And if you=
 just love crazy bits of juxtaposed text=2C you want this <a href=3D"https=
://kottke.org/18/02/a-winter-olympics-wrap-up-written-with-a-predictive-te=
xt-keyboard" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;"=
>Winter Olympics wrap-up written on a predictive text keyboard</a>. I for=
 one cannot wait for speed torah-reading to become a thing.</p>

<h2 class=3D"null" style=3D"color: #F00A0A;font-size: 22px;line-height: 27=
px;font-weight: bold;margin: 35px 0 10px;">You&#39;re probably doing this=
 wrong</h2>

<p style=3D"margin: 0 0 15px;">You might know you should <a href=3D"https:=
//twitter.com/kottke/status/968540231178731521" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">sneeze or cough into the inside of you=
r elbow</a>=2C not your hands. You should know to <a href=3D"https://twitt=
er.com/kottke/status/968155724810477568" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000;font-weight: bold;">fact-check things before you share them on so=
cial media</a>=2C although I bet we&#39;ve all been embarrassed at least o=
nce. It would help if <a href=3D"https://kottke.org/18/02/were-all-addicte=
d-to-the-smartphone-slot-machines-in-our-pockets" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000;font-weight: bold;">we used our smart phones=2C um=2C s=
marter</a>. But did you know that you&#39;re probably <a href=3D"https://t=
witter.com/kottke/status/968523623551193088" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000;font-weight: bold;">bending over wrong</a>? It&#39;s not at y=
our waist=2C or even with your legs; you should be bending with your hips.=
 (In other words=2C you&#39;ve got to stick your butt out.) This GIF shows=
 you how:</p>

